name: Kniddelen
short_description: Traditional to Luxembourg, these hearty dumplings are crafted from a rich blend of flour, eggs, and milk, then dropped into boiling water until they rise. Served with crispy bacon, they offer a comforting, savory delight.

name: Huesenziwwi
short_description: Marinated hare pieces simmer in a rich red wine sauce, thickened with hare's blood and enhanced by onions and sour cream. A hearty dish steeped in Luxembourg's culinary tradition, it's a must-try for game lovers.

name: Judd mat gaardebounen
short_description: Smoked collar of pork, tender and flavorful, pairs beautifully with fresh fava beans, leeks, and carrots in this beloved Luxembourgish specialty. A comforting taste of national pride!

name: Gromperekichelcher
short_description: Luxembourg’s beloved potato pancakes combine grated potatoes, shallots, and garlic, all expertly fried until golden. Each bite delivers a crispy exterior and a flavorful, tender center, perfect for snacking at local festivals.

name: Bouneschlupp
short_description: Luxembourg's beloved Bouneschlupp bursts with the hearty flavors of green beans, tender potatoes, and smoky bacon, creating a comforting bowl of tradition. Regional twists add delightful surprises like carrots and leeks.

name: Jambon en croute
short_description: Luxembourg's culinary gem features succulent smoked ham wrapped in a flaky pastry crust, baked to golden perfection. Each bite delivers a delightful blend of savory and rich flavors, celebrating the region's hearty traditions.

name: Friture de la Moselle
short_description: Originating from Luxembourg's Moselle River, these bite-sized treasures are lightly battered and fried to a perfect golden crisp, offering a delightful crunch and fresh, delicate flavors in every bite.

name: Träipen
short_description: Luxembourg's traditional blood sausage combines rich pork offal with savory cabbage, onions, and hearty stale bread. Each slice delivers a bold, flavorful experience steeped in local heritage.

name: Quetschentaart
short_description: Luxembourg's beloved autumn treat features a buttery crust filled with luscious damson plums, perfectly balancing sweet and tart flavors. A slice of tradition, it embodies the essence of fall.

name: Lëtzebuerger Grillwurscht
short_description: A beloved staple at Luxembourg's summer barbecues, these juicy sausages blend pork and veal with aromatic spices, grilled to perfection for a smoky, savory delight.

name: Rieslingspaschtéit
short_description: A beloved Luxembourgish tradition, this savory pie features a flaky pastry enveloping a rich pâté-like filling infused with aromatic Riesling aspic. Each bite delivers a delightful blend of textures and flavors.

name: Luxembourgish Esaü Soup
short_description: Hearty and comforting, this traditional Luxembourgish lentil stew blends earthy flavors of lentils with aromatic onions, carrots, celery, and leeks, creating a warm embrace of taste in every bowl.

name: Pâté Gaumais
short_description: Originating from the Gaume region of Luxembourg, this savory pie features tender marinated pork enveloped in a golden yeast dough, infused with aromatic spices for a hearty, flavorful experience.

name: Kuddelfleck
short_description: Luxembourg's Kuddelfleck showcases a rich heritage of resourcefulness, transforming tender tripes into a crispy delight. Coated in breadcrumbs and fried to golden perfection, it offers a savory crunch with every bite.

name: Kriibsen
short_description: Luxembourg's beloved kriibsen showcases fresh crayfish, cleaned and cooked in a savory sauce of finely chopped vegetables and aromatic herbs, offering a taste of local culinary tradition.

name: Mummentaart
short_description: Luxembourg's Mummentaart features a flaky crust enveloping a warm, cinnamon-spiced apple filling. This traditional tart celebrates autumn harvests, offering a delightful balance of sweetness and spice.

name: Feiersténgszalot
short_description: Originating from Luxembourg, this hearty meat salad combines tender beef, hard-boiled eggs, and zesty cornichons, all tossed in a tangy mustard vinaigrette for a deliciously satisfying bite.

name: Stäerzelen
short_description: Luxembourg’s beloved Stäerzelen features tender dumplings crafted from buckwheat flour, boiled to perfection. Their nutty flavor offers a comforting taste of tradition in every bite.

name: Verwurelter
short_description: Luxembourg's beloved Verwurelter features fluffy, knot-shaped donuts, deep-fried to golden perfection. A rich blend of butter and warm milk creates a sweet, indulgent treat steeped in local tradition.

name: Hong am rèisleck
short_description: A beloved Luxembourgish specialty, tender chicken is seared in butter and enveloped in a rich, creamy Riesling and cognac sauce. Each bite offers a delightful blend of local flavors and culinary tradition.

name: Tierteg
short_description: Luxembourg’s beloved Tierteg features crispy potato pancakes made from leftover mashed potatoes and tangy sauerkraut, all fried to golden perfection. Each bite offers a delightful blend of savory and slightly sour flavors.

name: F'rell am rèisleck
short_description: Freshwater trout is expertly fried in butter, then enveloped in a rich, creamy Riesling sauce, showcasing Luxembourg's culinary heritage with every savory bite.

name: Hiecht mat Kraiderzooss
short_description: Poached pike, a cherished Luxembourgian specialty, delights with a vibrant green sauce infused with Riesling wine. Each bite offers a fresh, herbaceous flavor that celebrates the region's culinary heritage.

name: Öennenzop
short_description: Luxembourg’s Öennenzop delights with a rich blend of sweet, sautéed onions simmered in vegetable stock, white wine, and aromatic caraway seeds. Served piping hot, it’s a comforting local favorite.
